[{"id":"VH861252","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><include href=\"../Passage/VH846539.qti.xml\" xmlns:xi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude\"></include></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">The poem is structured as which of the following?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VH861252_rubric","features":[{"type":"sharedpassage","html":"<div class=\"stimulus_reference\" xmlns=\"http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/apip/apipv1p0/qtiitem/imsqti_v2p2\" xmlns:xsi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance\"><p class=\"lead_in\"><span class=\"compose_cluster_phrase type:ordinal\"></span>     Read the following poem carefully before you choose your answers.</p><p class=\"introduction passage-intro\">George Herbert (1593–1633) was one of the English metaphysical poets. In 1630, he was ordained an Anglican priest and made rector at Bemerton. His collected poetry was not published until after his death, when his friend Nicholas Ferrar had it published as <span class=\"formatted_text font_style:italic\">The Temple</span> (1633).</p><div class=\"passage\"><div class=\"poetry style:1\"><div class=\"title\"><p class=\"title_line passage-title\">Time</p></div><div class=\"verse\"><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\"> </span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>Meeting with Time, “Slack thing,” said I,</span><br/><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\"> </span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>“Thy scythe<span class=\"footnote\" tabindex=\"0\"><span class=\"footnote_mark\">1</span><span class=\"footnote_text\">scythe: long-handled blade used for cutting grass or grain by hand.</span></span> is dull; whet<span class=\"footnote\" tabindex=\"0\"><span class=\"footnote_mark\">2</span><span class=\"footnote_text\">whet: sharpen.</span></span> it for shame.”</span><br/><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\"> </span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>“No marvel, sir,” he did reply,</span><br/><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\"> </span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>“If it at length deserve some blame;</span><br/><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\">5</span><span class=\"indent indent_2\"></span>But where one man would have me grind it,</span><br/><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\"> </span><span class=\"indent indent_2\"></span>Twenty for one too sharp do find it.”</span><br/></div><div class=\"verse\"><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\"> </span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>“Perhaps some such of old did pass,</span><br/><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\"> </span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>Who above all things loved this life;</span><br/><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\"> </span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>To whom thy scythe a hatchet was,</span><br/><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\">10</span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>Which now is but a pruning knife.</span><br/><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\"> </span><span class=\"indent indent_2\"></span>Christ’s coming<span class=\"footnote\" tabindex=\"0\"><span class=\"footnote_mark\">3</span><span class=\"footnote_text\">From a Christian perspective, death is viewed not as an endpoint but as passage to the afterlife. Christ’s redemptive suffering enables the reunification of the soul with God after death.</span></span> hath made man thy debtor,</span><br/><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\"> </span><span class=\"indent indent_2\"></span>Since by thy cutting he grows better.</span><br/></div><div class=\"verse\"><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\"> </span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>“And in his blessing thou art blessed,</span><br/><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\"> </span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>For where thou only wert before</span><br/><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\">15</span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>An executioner at best,</span><br/><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\"> </span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>Thou art a gardener now, and more,</span><br/><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\"> </span><span class=\"indent indent_2\"></span>An usher<span class=\"footnote\" tabindex=\"0\"><span class=\"footnote_mark\">4</span><span class=\"footnote_text\">usher: one who escorts persons to their seats</span></span> to convey our souls</span><br/><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\"> </span><span class=\"indent indent_2\"></span>Beyond the utmost stars and poles.</span><br/></div><div class=\"verse\"><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\"> </span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>“And this is that makes life so long,</span><br/><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\">20</span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>While it detains us from our God.</span><br/><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\"> </span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>Ev’n pleasures here increase the wrong,</span><br/><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\"> </span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>And length of days lengthens the rod<span class=\"footnote\" tabindex=\"0\"><span class=\"footnote_mark\">5</span><span class=\"footnote_text\">rod: shoot, branch; instrument of punishment</span></span>.</span><br/><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\"> </span><span class=\"indent indent_2\"></span>Who wants<span class=\"footnote\" tabindex=\"0\"><span class=\"footnote_mark\">6</span><span class=\"footnote_text\">wants: lacks</span></span> the place where God doth dwell</span><br/><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\"> </span><span class=\"indent indent_2\"></span>Partakes already half of hell.</span><br/></div><div class=\"verse\"><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\">25</span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>“Of what strange length must that needs be,</span><br/><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\"> </span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>Which ev’n eternity excludes!”—</span><br/><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\"> </span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>Thus far Time heard me patiently,</span><br/><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\"> </span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>Then chafing<span class=\"footnote\" tabindex=\"0\"><span class=\"footnote_mark\">7</span><span class=\"footnote_text\">chafing: showing irritation</span></span> said, “This man deludes:</span><br/><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\"> </span><span class=\"indent indent_2\"></span>What do I here before his door?</span><br/><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\">30</span><span class=\"indent indent_2\"></span>He doth not crave less time, but more.”</span><br/></div></div></div></div>"}],"choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">A monologue</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">A conversation</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">An announcement</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">A hypothesis</p>"],"answer":2}]